t you may be liable to investigation and potentially to enforcement action, including prosecution, if you knowingly submit false, misleading, or otherwise inaccurate data&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;/td&gt; &lt;/tr&gt; &lt;/table&gt; &lt;p&gt; For guidance on fish species please see: &lt;a href=""http://www.fao.org/fishery/collection/asfis/en""&gt; http://www.fao.org/fishery/collection/asfis/en &lt;/a&gt;. To see a list of licensed fishing vessels please see: &lt;a href=""https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/uk-vessel-lists""&gt; https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/uk-vessel-lists &lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The mandatory fields you must complete are as follows:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; Section 2: fishing vessel name, call sign/PLN, fishing licence number, fishing gear&lt;br&gt; Section 3: species, product code, catch area(s), net catch weight in kg&lt;br&gt; Section 5: Name and signature of the master of the vessel&lt;br&gt; Section 8: Name of exporter and date of acceptance&lt;br&gt; Annex 1: exporter name and address &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; Use &lt;a href=""https://www.gov.uk/guidance/temporary-fish-exports-guidance""&gt; https://www.gov.uk/guidance/temporary-fish-exports-guidance &lt;/a&gt; for additional information. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;/body&gt; &lt;/html&gt;"]</InArgument>
